text.section:
Except as provided in subsection (f) of this section, with respect to any endangered species of fish, no person may:
Export the species from the State;
Take the species within the State;
Possess, process, sell, or offer for sale, deliver, carry, transport, or ship the species by any means; or
Violate any regulation pertaining to the conservation of the species or to any threatened species of wildlife listed pursuant to this subsection and adopted by the Secretary pursuant to authority provided by this section.
